text: Sportklub Sturm Graz is an Austrian football club from Graz, Styria. The club was started in 1909 but the women's section was started in 2011. Sturm Graz (women section) plays in the ÖFB-Frauenliga, the highest league in women's football in Austria. ==History== The club was founded in 2011 after taking over FC Stattegg's women's team. They started in the 2nd Women's League East. In the 2012-13 season they were promoted to the ÖFB Frauenliga. 2015/16 the finished 2nd and qualified for the UEFA Women's Champions League . ===Current team=== ÖFB Vereine:Kader (German) ===Coaching staff=== * Christian Lang Headcoach * Emily Cancienne Assistant coach * Daniel Gutschi Goalkeeper coach ÖFB.at Betreuer (German) ==Honours== * ÖFB-Frauenliga runners-up (3) : 2015-16, 2016–17, 2018–19 ==Record in UEFA Women's Champions League== ===Summary=== Pld W D L GF GA Last season played 8 3 0 5 14 23 2019–20 ===By season=== Season Round Opponent Home Away Agg 2016–17 Round of 32 Zürich 0–6 0–3 0-9 2017–18 Qualifying round Noroc Nimoreni 4–0 2nd of 4 2017–18 NSA Sofia 3–1 2017–18 Apollon Limassol 1–4 2019–20 Qualifying round Braga 0–2 3rd of 4 2019–20 Rīgas FS 4–0 2019–20 Apollon Limassol 2–7 ==References== Category:Women's football in Austria Category:Austrian football clubs Category:Football clubs of Styria Category:2011 establishments in Europe Category:2010s establishments in Austria
